properties.name: Firefox Crop Circle
properties.description: Posted by HuslageDoes the sudden appearance of a Firefox crop circle imply which browser extraterrestrials prefer? We don\'t know, but it was still fun to make! Constructed by local Firefox fans and the same team that created the Firefox mural from cornstarch and kool-aid and launched the Firefox weather balloon, the Firefox Crop Circle project shows that we have so much passion for Firefox that we want it to be visible from space! Planned in under two weeks and completed in under 24 hours, the crop circle had a final diameter of 220 feet. We constructed the circle in an oat field near Amity, Oregon, where it was completely invisible from the road but unmistakable from the sky. Our team consisted of 12 people, mainly OSU students, and we carefully stomped down oats from 3:30pm Friday afternoon until 2:30am, putting on the finishing touches between 7:30am and 11:00am Saturday, August 12. night shot Matt and John, Mozilla video interns, came up with the idea a few weeks beforehand. Fueled by the enthusiasm of Asa Dotzler at Mozilla, suddenly the crop circle was within reach. While at OSCON 2006 in Portland, the three of them ran into members of the OSLUG, and things really started to take shape.

properties.name: The Geo Chain
properties.description: Posted by Jason The Goe Chain is an attempt to wrap the world with a chain. Anyone is invited to go there and add some chain, eventually it\'ll grow and grow and grow. --------- Directions to the Geo Chain Please respect the private residences nearby 1) Locate the town of Joshua Tree on a map and go there (2+ hour drive east of Los Angeles, CA) 2) Just east of town, on the main 29 Palms Highway, you will see Joshua Tree Bail Bonds 3) Turn South on Neptune Avenue and you will be on a road like this. Don\'t be afraid, you\'re almost there 4) Up the hill the dirt road becomes a T, go left. 5) Stay on the road for about 1/10 of a mile until it ends at a little turnaround. Stop. Head directly east over the rocks, in line with the road, right under the power lines, and there\'s the post with the beginning of the chain. or: Send lengths of chain to: Robert Barrus (For the Geo Chain) 351 Neimeyer Yucca Valley, Calif. 92284

properties.name: “Don't Go Any Further”
properties.description: Posted by Kylebravo   4300 St. Claude, New Orleans, LA One thing I love about New Orleans is how all over the city the street names are cemented into the sidewalks in tile. At this spot there\'s tiles in the sidewalk that say “DON\'T GO ANY FURTHER.” Why is this here? Why can\'t we go any further? Needless to say, no one heeds this mysterious warning. I think most people probably have never even noticed it.
